      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i get the bond strength part. so if the bond fails, the steel just slides out. are there any specific ways engineers prevent that? like is it just about the surface of the rebar or something about the mix itself? also is there any way things can go wrong \"under the surface\" where you can't see it until it's too late?",
